redis-rs-port (valkey-rs / Valdr)
=================================

This project is an AI-assisted port (a derivative work — a translation from
C to Rust) of Valkey, the BSD-3-Clause fork of Redis maintained by the Linux
Foundation, pinned at Valkey 9.1.0 (commit c9e8005e9; see harness/source.toml).
It is not a clean-room re-implementation: the port is produced by translating
the upstream C source with structural fidelity, so it is a derivative of that
source and is governed by the upstream license below.

This port is distributed under the BSD 3-Clause License. The port's own
copyright and license appear in LICENSE; the upstream copyright notices, which
the BSD 3-Clause License requires be retained in redistributions of source,
are reproduced verbatim here.

The pinned, unmodified upstream source is preserved under reference/valkey/;
upstream's full COPYING (including bundled-dependency licenses) lives at
reference/valkey/COPYING.


